WEBVTT

00:04.081 --> 00:07.768
I think it had a lot to do with the faculty. And we had 
a great faculty relationship. I was never denied

00:11.856 --> 00:18.870
any sort of advising that I felt that I needed. I was 
guided quite well. Now, too, you've got to add to

00:20.292 --> 00:22.697
that the question even with the tremendous growth 
that the university population experienced

00:23.588 --> 00:28.976
during that time. Needless to say, the faculty 
pace could not keep up with it in terms of

00:28.996 --> 00:35.666
student-teacher ratio. But most of the colleges, 
some better than others, did a great job of making

00:36.066 --> 00:44.579
it work anyway. And there was, I mean, I don't know 
of a time that I needed to either go see a professor

00:51.938 --> 01:13.738
in one of my classes, or excuse me, I cannot 
