11:08.750 --> 11:28.450
decided that he was going to write a freshman 
chemistry text that was based on a programmed

11:08.750 --> 11:28.450
learning concept, which basically is you sort of 
like take chapters of stuff and have self-tests

11:08.750 --> 11:28.450
associated with each chapter and the sort of 
building process that goes on in the program

11:08.750 --> 11:28.450
learning aspect of it. And Rod had written this 
chemistry book. And actually, I remember it quite

11:31.313 --> 11:38.884
well because it had been typed and had been reduced 
